'''''Young Jedi Knights: Return to Ord Mantell''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the twelfth book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[May]] [[1998]]. It also includes a twelve-page preview of the next book in the series, [[Young Jedi Knights: Trouble on Cloud City|''Trouble on Cloud City'']]. The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Under Black Sun]]'' ([[1999]]).

==Publisher's summary==
'''Jacen and Jaina'''

''When the Galactic Empire died, they were born—a new hope for the New Republic. The young twins of Han Solo and Princess Leia have grown strong with the Force, thwarting the evil Nolaa Tarkona and destroying the Emperor's Plague. Now, with their friends Lowbacca the Wookiee and Tenel Ka, the future heroes of an already legendary saga continue their training.''

''Han Solo's past is about to catch up with him. When he and the twins take the ''Millennium Falcon'' to Ord Mantell for a high-speed race, they meet a battle-hungry woman wielding a lightsaber. Her name is Anja Gallandro, and she knows more about Han's history than he likes. But Anja Gallandro guards an even more devastating secret—a secret that could mean disaster for the entire Solo family''.

==Plot summary==
[[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] studies are briefly interrupted when [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] arrives on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] and invites [[Solo twins (disambiguation)|his kids]] and their friends to accompany him to [[Ord Mantell/Legends|Ord Mantell]], where he's been named [[Grand Marshal of the Blockade Runners Derby]]. During the event, a young [[Gender/Legends|woman]] brandishing a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] confronts Han, claiming that he [[Death/Legends|killed]] her [[Parent/Legends|father]]. It is [[Anja Gallandro]], daughter of the late, infamous [[Gunslinger/Legends|gunslinger]]. Han tries to explain he didn't kill [[Gallandro/Legends|Gallandro]], but the bitter Anja doesn't believe him. She has grown up an orphan on the war-ravaged world of [[Anobis]], and Han tries to improve her a lot by voyaging to the beleaguered [[Planet/Legends|planet]] to help settle the conflict. Little does Han know that Anja is working for [[Czethros]], a [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] who wants Han dead. Czethros keeps Anja strung out on [[Andris/Legends|andris]], an addictive [[Spice/Legends|spice]] that can boost one's senses and reflexes to Jedi-like levels.

==Continuity==
''Young Jedi Knights: Return to Ord Mantell'' gives [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]] and [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]]'s age as sixteen [[Standard year/Legends|year]]s old. However, since ''Return to Ord Mantell'' is set in [[24 ABY/Legends|24 ABY]] and they were [[Reproduction/Legends|born]] in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]],<ref name="TERC" /> the [[Solo twins (disambiguation)|Solo children]] cannot be older than fifteen.

[[Anja Gallandro]] is the daughter of the [[Gallandro/Legends|gunslinger]] featured in [[Brian Daley]]'s ''[[Han Solo's Revenge]]'' ([[1979]]) and ''[[Han Solo and the Lost Legacy]]'' ([[1980]]). The [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Czethros]] was originally intended to be [[Skorr/Legends|Skorr]], the titular antagonist from the [[1981]] [[Star Wars (comic strip)|comic strip]] [[The Bounty Hunter of Ord Mantell]] by [[Archie Goodwin]] and [[Al Williamson]]. At the eleventh hour, however, editors realized that Skorr [[Death/Legends|died]] at the end of the newspaper strip in [[1984]], so Skorr was hastily rewritten as new character Czethros.<ref name="TERC" />

